  "prompt": "What was the universe before Big Bang?",
  "response": "The nature of the universe before the Big Bang is a topic of ongoing scientific research and philosophical speculation. Currently, there are several theoretical perspectives:\n\n1. Scientific Limitations\n- Our current understanding of physics breaks down at the moment of the Big Bang\n- Existing scientific models cannot definitively describe what existed \"before\"\n\n2. Prominent Theoretical Perspectives\n- Quantum Fluctuation: The universe may have emerged from a quantum state of potential\n- Eternal Inflation Theory: Suggests our universe is one of many in a multiverse\n- Cyclic Model: Proposes universes repeatedly expand and contract\n- String Theory: Suggests potential pre-existing dimensional states\n\n3. Known Uncertainties\n- No direct observational evidence exists about pre-Big Bang conditions\n- Extremely high temperatures and densities prevent traditional scientific investigation\n- Current physics cannot describe the initial singularity\n\n4. Philosophical Considerations\n- Some argue the concept of \"before\" might be meaningless without time as we understand it\n- The Big Bang might represent the origin of time itself\n\nScientists continue researching this profound question, but definitive answers remain elusive. Current understanding acknowledges significant limitations in comprehending pre-Big Bang existence.",
